00:43:19,192 --> 00:43:21,786
Go easy on that.
I'm not sure that he's ready.

762
00:43:21,862 --> 00:43:23,625
FLASH:
We'll talk about it first.

763
00:43:23,697 --> 00:43:25,562
We need him. All right, um...

764
00:43:25,632 --> 00:43:26,656
are we still on
for tomorrow night?

765
00:43:26,733 --> 00:43:27,995
Yeah.

766
00:43:28,068 --> 00:43:29,729
O.K., I'll meet you
at the bus stop at seven.

767
00:43:29,803 --> 00:43:32,328
Yeah, well, you make it eight...
and you be there!

768
00:43:32,406 --> 00:43:33,805
O.K., eight.

769
00:43:34,875 --> 00:43:35,864
[Hangs up phone]

770
00:43:37,411 --> 00:43:39,345
- Hello?
- [Dial tone]

771
00:43:39,413 --> 00:43:40,402
Flash?

772
00:43:40,981 --> 00:43:41,970
[Phone beeps]

773
00:43:42,983 --> 00:43:44,575
[Crickets chirp]

774
00:43:54,661 --> 00:43:55,650
[Crying]

775
00:44:02,402 --> 00:44:04,802
[Sobbing]

776
00:44:54,955 --> 00:44:56,252
Hey, Mickey.

777
00:44:56,323 --> 00:44:59,315
MICKEY: Hello, kid.
Uh... where's Flash?

778
00:45:00,293 --> 00:45:01,282
Well, he's...

779
00:45:03,663 --> 00:45:05,654
I really need your help, Mickey.

780
00:45:06,733 --> 00:45:09,998
I... I'm no good to you, son.

781
00:45:10,937 --> 00:45:12,268
It's too far gone.

782
00:45:12,939 --> 00:45:15,908
No, listen, can...
Can you just hear me out?

783
00:45:15,976 --> 00:45:18,240
Can I, can I come in
for a minute?

784
00:45:18,311 --> 00:45:20,040
Yeah... of course.

785
00:45:23,450 --> 00:45:25,680
Flash said you'd be back.

786
00:45:36,496 --> 00:45:38,464
Hey, Cameron...

787
00:45:38,532 --> 00:45:40,523
pick up one of them boxes.

788
00:45:41,301 --> 00:45:42,962
No, no, the bigger one.

789
00:45:43,970 --> 00:45:45,164
You called me Cameron.

790
00:45:45,238 --> 00:45:46,262
It's your name, isn't it?

791
00:45:48,074 --> 00:45:50,474
ANNOUNCER ON TV: Wells
at the line for his second shot.

792
00:45:50,544 --> 00:45:52,375
It's up... no good!

793
00:45:52,445 --> 00:45:54,606
Kicked out back, rebounded
there, pass outlet...

794
00:45:54,681 --> 00:45:56,410
MAN: Pass the ball!

795
00:45:56,483 --> 00:45:58,417
Ah, that ain't no foul!

796
00:45:58,485 --> 00:46:00,851
That ain't no foul!
Thank God it's Shaq.

797
00:46:00,921 --> 00:46:02,786
Thank God it's Shaq.

798
00:46:02,856 --> 00:46:04,847
Hey, whoa, ho.
Hey, whoa, hey.

799
00:46:05,425 --> 00:46:08,019
Expendables, Stage 10.
The kid's with me.

800
00:46:08,094 --> 00:46:09,493
MAN: You got I. D?

801
00:46:09,563 --> 00:46:10,552
No problemo.

802
00:46:11,498 --> 00:46:12,760
What's the score?

803
00:46:12,833 --> 00:46:14,630
Lakers by two, double overtime.

804
00:46:14,701 --> 00:46:16,896
Bingo, Shaq just missed
another free throw!

805
00:46:16,970 --> 00:46:18,301
Some things never change.

806
00:46:19,206 --> 00:46:20,798
Haven't seen you before.
You new?

807
00:46:20,874 --> 00:46:22,205
I'm anything but new...

808
00:46:23,310 --> 00:46:25,437
meaning I'm old. Get it?

809
00:46:25,512 --> 00:46:26,672
Oh, yeah, oh, yeah.

810
00:46:26,746 --> 00:46:28,008
Hey, Stage 10,
right around the corner.

811
00:46:28,081 --> 00:46:29,070
FLASH: Merry Christmas.

812
00:46:29,149 --> 00:46:30,946
MAN: Yeah,
Merry Christmas to you too.

813
00:46:31,017 --> 00:46:33,577
? Ooh ?

814
00:46:33,653 --> 00:46:36,121
? Lonely, lonely, lonely ?

815
00:46:36,189 --> 00:46:40,091
? I'm waiting for you... ?

816
00:46:41,995 --> 00:46:44,759
? Ooh ?

817
00:46:44,831 --> 00:46:47,061
? Lonely, lonely, lonely ?

818
00:46:48,635 --> 00:46:50,227
CAMERON: Where's Stage 10?

819
00:46:50,303 --> 00:46:53,272
FLASH:
We're not going to Stage 10.

820
00:46:53,340 --> 00:46:55,069
Come on.

821
00:46:55,141 --> 00:46:56,130
[Clears throat]

822
00:46:56,209 --> 00:46:57,574
Lose the box.

823
00:47:03,783 --> 00:47:05,410
CAMERON:
How hot do the lights get?

824
00:47:05,485 --> 00:47:06,474
FLASH: Hot.

825
00:47:07,320 --> 00:47:10,050
Are these c-stands?
I love c-stands!

826
00:47:15,328 --> 00:47:17,888
So can we actually come back
and grab some of this stuff?

827
00:47:17,964 --> 00:47:19,329
[Flash grunts]

828
00:47:19,399 --> 00:47:21,526
CAMERON: This place
is actually pretty creepy.

829
00:47:21,601 --> 00:47:22,932
Seems like the kind of place
that would be haunted.

830
00:47:24,437 --> 00:47:25,836
[Flash grunts]

831
00:47:25,906 --> 00:47:27,396
What would happen
if we got caught in here?

832
00:47:27,474 --> 00:47:30,034
FLASH: Uh...
well, it's been a long time...

833
00:47:30,110 --> 00:47:31,737
but I'm sure it's still here.

834
00:47:31,811 --> 00:47:32,800
What's still here?

835
00:47:34,347 --> 00:47:35,678
Hmm...

836
00:47:37,217 --> 00:47:40,118
FLASH:
They must have sealed it off.

837
00:47:40,186 --> 00:47:42,814
CAMERON: Well, then we should
probably head back then, right?

838
00:47:42,889 --> 00:47:44,754
FLASH: Not likely.

839
00:47:47,427 --> 00:47:48,416
[Door thumps]

840
00:47:49,296 --> 00:47:50,627
[Door creaks]

841
00:47:52,365 --> 00:47:53,696
It's, it's still here.

842
00:47:54,868 --> 00:47:57,098
[Talking to himself]

843
00:48:02,642 --> 00:48:03,631
[Wood clatters]

844
00:48:05,745 --> 00:48:06,769
[Wings flap]

845
00:48:06,846 --> 00:48:08,711
CAMERON: Is this, like,
breaking and entering?

846
00:48:08,782 --> 00:48:11,751
FLASH: Yeah, who broke in?
The door just opened.

847
00:48:15,655 --> 00:48:16,644
FLASH: Oh, shit.

848
00:48:18,591 --> 00:48:20,218
Where's the goddamn
fuse box?

849
00:48:29,436 --> 00:48:30,460
How'd you do that?

850
00:48:30,537 --> 00:48:32,869
I'm a gaffer, for Christ's sake.

851
00:48:32,939 --> 00:48:33,928
Oh, right.

852
00:48:34,674 --> 00:48:36,335
Well, this is it.

853
00:48:38,645 --> 00:48:41,136
This is our room,
the crew's room.

854
00:48:41,214 --> 00:48:43,148
Yeah, used to be
the old prop room.

855
00:48:43,216 --> 00:48:45,150
We cleaned it up and,
uh, made it our own.

856
00:48:45,218 --> 00:48:46,549
This is so cool.

857
00:48:47,687 --> 00:48:49,655
How is it still here?

858
00:48:49,723 --> 00:48:51,384
Uh, the present management
doesn't know about this room.

859
00:48:51,458 --> 00:48:52,550
Never did.

860
00:48:52,625 --> 00:48:54,650
Thank god. They'd turn it
into a Starbucks.

861
00:48:54,728 --> 00:48:56,127
CAMERON: Yeah, right.

862
00:48:56,196 --> 00:48:58,528
So this place
was like a clubhouse?

863
00:48:59,032 --> 00:49:00,590
FLASH: Yeah, sort of.

864
00:49:00,667 --> 00:49:03,033
But it was a tough club
to get into.

865
00:49:03,103 --> 00:49:05,901
No above-the-line wankers,
that's for sure.

866
00:49:05,972 --> 00:49:06,996
Above the line?

867
00:49:07,073 --> 00:49:10,338
Eh, producers, directors,
writers, actors, those creeps.

868
00:49:12,412 --> 00:49:13,902
So you know all these people?

869
00:49:13,980 --> 00:49:16,972
Most of them.
A lot of them are dead.

870
00:49:17,817 --> 00:49:19,978
Uh, but these are my friends.

871
00:49:20,053 --> 00:49:23,614
Hey, that's me with the crew
of, uh, Citizen Kane.

872
00:49:23,690 --> 00:49:25,157
You worked on Citizen Kane?

873
00:49:25,225 --> 00:49:27,420
Yeah... the skinny guy
in the middle.

874
00:49:27,494 --> 00:49:29,826
CAMERON: So amazing.
Is Orson Welles there?

875
00:49:30,497 --> 00:49:33,466
These are crew-only photos,
for Christ's sake.

876
00:49:33,533 --> 00:49:35,501
Oh, so no directors,
no wankers?

877
00:49:35,568 --> 00:49:36,557
Right.

878
00:49:37,637 --> 00:49:39,832
I always wanted to be
a wanker... director.

879
00:49:39,906 --> 00:49:42,602
A director, huh?
The man in the chair, huh?

880
00:49:42,675 --> 00:49:43,733
I guess.

881
00:49:43,810 --> 00:49:45,141
You guess?

882
00:49:45,211 --> 00:49:47,236
The man in the chair
can't ever be a guesser.

883
00:49:47,313 --> 00:49:48,541
He's gotta make decisions.

884
00:49:48,615 --> 00:49:49,946
You know, boom, boom,
boom, boom, boom.

885
00:49:50,016 --> 00:49:51,347
He's gotta know
what he's doing.

886
00:49:51,418 --> 00:49:54,182
Frank Capra says, "If you're
half right, you'll be a genius."

887
00:49:54,254 --> 00:49:56,381
Frank Capra, cool director.
Money!

888
00:49:56,456 --> 00:49:58,287
Hello? [Mutters]

889
00:49:59,259 --> 00:50:00,988
CAMERON:
Did you ever direct a movie?

890
00:50:01,061 --> 00:50:02,790
Yeah, I got close to it
a couple of times...

891
00:50:02,862 --> 00:50:08,095
but it wasn't exactly my cup of,
uh, tea... if you get my drift.

892
00:50:08,168 --> 00:50:11,160
Oh, you had a little booze,
drinking problem...

893
00:50:11,237 --> 00:50:12,226
thing, problem?

894
00:50:13,273 --> 00:50:15,605
Oh, yeah, I had my...
[Chuckles]

895
00:50:15,675 --> 00:50:19,202
fair share of, mmm,
missed opportunities.

896
00:50:23,817 --> 00:50:24,806
Flash?

897
00:50:24,884 --> 00:50:25,873
Yeah, kid.

898
00:50:30,557 --> 00:50:33,492
You're the only one who
can help me out with this.

899
00:50:35,328 --> 00:50:37,660
And I want to know everything
there is to know.

900
00:50:37,730 --> 00:50:40,426
Teach me how to make movies...

901
00:50:40,500 --> 00:50:43,060
how to watch them...
everything.

902
00:50:43,136 --> 00:50:45,400
It means
that much to you, huh?

903
00:50:45,472 --> 00:50:47,440
To be the man in the chair?

904
00:50:47,507 --> 00:50:50,169
Yeah, it does... everything.

905
00:50:50,243 --> 00:50:52,541
Will you be willing
to pay the price?

906
00:50:53,680 --> 00:50:55,580
Cigars and Wild Turkey?

907
00:50:55,648 --> 00:50:57,548
No, no, no.
Well, yeah, yeah, of cour...

908
00:50:57,617 --> 00:50:58,606
[Sharply] No.

909
00:51:00,019 --> 00:51:02,010
I mean, the real price.

910
00:51:04,023 --> 00:51:05,456
CAMERON: What's that?

911
00:51:05,525 --> 00:51:08,016
A promise... to me...

912
00:51:09,662 --> 00:51:12,563
that if you ever make it,
you won't crap on people...

913
00:51:12,632 --> 00:51:14,293
like Mickey and the others...

914
00:51:15,301 --> 00:51:17,292
like these fine folks.

915
00:51:20,540 --> 00:51:25,534
And that you'll never forget
how and who...

916
00:51:27,147 --> 00:51:28,808
got you to the chair.

917
00:51:30,216 --> 00:51:31,877
Can you make that promise?

918
00:51:34,020 --> 00:51:35,510
Sure, Flash.

919
00:51:37,557 --> 00:51:39,286
Now we're talking Technicolor.

920
00:51:40,994 --> 00:51:43,792
Well, it'll actually
probably be 24p digital video.

921
00:51:43,863 --> 00:51:44,852
Yeah, whatever.

922
00:51:55,475 --> 00:51:57,409
- You know all these people?
- Yeah, most of them.

923
00:51:58,578 --> 00:52:00,136
Do you have a star?

924
00:52:00,213 --> 00:52:02,078
The only thing in the ground
with my name on it...

925
00:52:02,148 --> 00:52:03,638
will be a gravestone.

926
00:52:03,716 --> 00:52:05,149
Why? You made
some great movies.

927
00:52:05,218 --> 00:52:08,585
Oh, come on.
You gotta be famous, adored.

928
00:52:08,655 --> 00:52:09,952
- I'm neither.
- [Bell ringing]

929
00:52:10,023 --> 00:52:11,547
You should get a star just
for helping out me and Murphy.

930
00:52:11,624 --> 00:52:15,355
Hey, remember this.
The glitter ends at La Brea.

931
00:52:15,428 --> 00:52:16,793
What does that mean?

932
00:52:16,863 --> 00:52:20,162
You see the glitter that
the city puts in the pavement...

933
00:52:20,233 --> 00:52:22,599
- where the stars are, huh?
- Yeah?

934
00:52:22,669 --> 00:52:25,365
Well, look, it ends at La Brea.

935
00:52:26,472 --> 00:52:27,962
No stars, no glitter.

936
00:52:28,041 --> 00:52:30,566
In other words, uh,
it don't last forever...

937
00:52:30,643 --> 00:52:32,076
like fame in Hollywood.

938
00:52:32,145 --> 00:52:34,613
It lasts for only a second,
if at all.

939
00:52:34,681 --> 00:52:37,844
So don't friggin' worry
about gettin' famous.

940
00:52:37,917 --> 00:52:39,680
Get good at your job.

941
00:52:39,752 --> 00:52:42,380
If fame comes along, so be it.

942
00:52:42,455 --> 00:52:43,479
CAMERON:
You're famous to me.

943
00:52:43,556 --> 00:52:46,184
FLASH: That's because you
don't know anybody else.

944
00:52:55,568 --> 00:52:56,694
NURSE: Oh!

945
00:52:59,405 --> 00:53:00,736
YOGA INSTRUCTOR ON TV:
As you can see, we have...

946
00:53:00,807 --> 00:53:02,035
MAN: Oh, come on, Speed.
We're all trying to see that.

947
00:53:02,108 --> 00:53:05,703
Move back please, Speed,
so we can all see.

948
00:53:05,778 --> 00:53:06,767
What?

949
00:53:07,747 --> 00:53:09,146
MAN: Get out of the way.

950
00:53:13,052 --> 00:53:16,044
- Hey!
- Well, what's happening?

951
00:53:16,122 --> 00:53:18,113
- Flash, I was dancing.
- [Overlapping chatter]

952
00:53:19,058 --> 00:53:20,218
FLASH:
Wait a minute, wait a minute.

953
00:53:20,293 --> 00:53:21,726
Shut up! Shut up!

954
00:53:21,794 --> 00:53:23,785
I got something to tell you.

955
00:53:24,430 --> 00:53:26,227
We're going on location.

956
00:53:28,401 --> 00:53:30,232
It's time for my medication?

957
00:53:30,303 --> 00:53:31,292
[Murmuring]

958
00:53:32,505 --> 00:53:34,564
MAN 2:
No, we're going on location.

959
00:53:34,641 --> 00:53:37,337
- Oh, Speed.
- Not yet, we're not rolling.

960
00:53:38,544 --> 00:53:41,877
I just love location shooting!

961
00:53:41,948 --> 00:53:45,179
The hotels, the parties,
the fun, the dancing...

962
00:53:45,251 --> 00:53:46,843
Slut.

963
00:53:46,919 --> 00:53:48,443
Mrs. Erskine!

964
00:53:48,521 --> 00:53:49,510
Oh, she's a tramp!

965
00:53:49,589 --> 00:53:51,648
You silly old biddy.

966
00:53:51,724 --> 00:53:54,693
Why, your chariot's so low,
it's dragging the basement floor.

967
00:53:54,761 --> 00:53:55,785
Get a life.

968
00:53:55,862 --> 00:53:56,920
FLASH: Hey, hey, ladies...

969
00:53:56,996 --> 00:53:58,429
Is that Animal Planet?

970
00:53:58,498 --> 00:53:59,931
FLASH: Hey, hey ladies, relax.

971
00:53:59,999 --> 00:54:02,991
Ladies... we're not exactly
going on location...

972
00:54:03,069 --> 00:54:05,196
- but we are going into production.
- MAN: O.K.

973
00:54:05,271 --> 00:54:06,260
MRS ERSKINE:
Yeah, what's the rate?

974
00:54:06,339 --> 00:54:07,829
What did he say?

975
00:54:07,907 --> 00:54:09,374
That's great, that's hot.

976
00:54:09,442 --> 00:54:11,410
[Whistling] Let him talk!

977
00:54:13,046 --> 00:54:16,243
Well, I met a kid who needs
our help with his student film.

978
00:54:16,316 --> 00:54:18,409
- Hey, Flash!
- Yeah, Montana.

979
00:54:18,484 --> 00:54:19,951
What's he need?

980
00:54:20,019 --> 00:54:21,452
He needs your help
with wardrobe...

981
00:54:21,521 --> 00:54:23,648
and, Rich, he needs your help
with art direction.

982
00:54:23,723 --> 00:54:25,213
Speed can help with sound.

983
00:54:25,291 --> 00:54:27,782
- What?
- You can do the sound.

984
00:54:28,561 --> 00:54:30,461
Bernie here can give him
a hand with props.

985
00:54:30,530 --> 00:54:32,191
I'm retired.
I got out of the rat race...

986
00:54:32,265 --> 00:54:33,630
a long time ago, thank you.

987
00:54:33,700 --> 00:54:35,964
Butch can help with camera,
me with lighting...

988
00:54:36,035 --> 00:54:38,003
- and Big John with grip.
- You betcha.

989
00:54:38,071 --> 00:54:41,598
Oh, boy, does he have
the best crew in town.

990
00:54:41,674 --> 00:54:43,301
Well, the oldest crew, anyway.

991
00:54:43,376 --> 00:54:45,071
[Laughter]

992
00:54:45,144 --> 00:54:46,509
The what?

993
00:54:46,579 --> 00:54:50,345
And the only one
with a deaf sound mixer.

994
00:54:50,416 --> 00:54:53,442
- [Laughter]
- Oh, I heard that.

995
00:54:53,519 --> 00:54:56,010
Flash, I'm available.

996
00:54:56,089 --> 00:54:57,681
Newsflash!

997
00:54:57,757 --> 00:54:59,952
So, who's the kid?

998
00:55:00,026 --> 00:55:01,550
CAMERON: We're just
doing research. You'll be fine.

999
00:55:01,627 --> 00:55:03,720
MICKEY: I don't know, Cameron.

1000
00:55:03,796 --> 00:55:05,593
It's cool. You'll be all right.

1001
00:55:05,665 --> 00:55:08,998
Eh, Flash said you were
a pushy little so-and-so.

1002
00:55:12,071 --> 00:55:14,869
Don't be afraid, Mickey.
It's only a computer.

1003
00:55:14,941 --> 00:55:16,875
It's real easy, O. K?
Computers are really stupid.

1004
00:55:16,943 --> 00:55:18,274
They do exactly what
you tell them to.

1005
00:55:18,344 --> 00:55:21,040
That's what I'm afraid of,
what to tell them.

1006
00:55:21,114 --> 00:55:23,639
No problemo.
Check it out, we can Google.

1007
00:55:23,716 --> 00:55:24,705
Google?

1008
00:55:25,585 --> 00:55:27,450
Yeah, a lot of bloggers Google.

1009
00:55:27,520 --> 00:55:29,454
Bloggers that Google.

1010
00:55:29,522 --> 00:55:31,319
Or they Dogpile.

1011
00:55:31,391 --> 00:55:32,688
Dogpile.

1012
00:55:32,759 --> 00:55:35,922
Dogpile or a Hotbot
or Lycos, Linkslut...

1013
00:55:35,995 --> 00:55:37,724
