1281
01:11:17,336 --> 01:11:19,133
CAMERON: So that's our story.

1282
01:11:19,204 --> 01:11:21,263
It's about $5,000 in hard costs.

1283
01:11:22,240 --> 01:11:23,798
She died
a couple of years ago.

1284
01:11:23,875 --> 01:11:24,864
FLASH: I heard.

1285
01:11:25,744 --> 01:11:28,770
She was the greatest person
I ever knew.

1286
01:11:28,847 --> 01:11:31,782
[Chuckling]
Tell me something I don't know.

1287
01:11:31,850 --> 01:11:35,217
Uh, I can see that you
really miss her.

1288
01:11:37,155 --> 01:11:39,646
MOSS: It was two years ago.

1289
01:11:39,725 --> 01:11:41,352
Seems like yesterday to me.

1290
01:11:45,397 --> 01:11:46,591
Cigar?

1291
01:11:46,665 --> 01:11:48,724
Eh, don't mind if I do.

1292
01:11:54,773 --> 01:11:55,762
[Spits]

1293
01:11:57,342 --> 01:11:58,536
Cameron?

1294
01:11:58,610 --> 01:12:01,170
Oh, no, thanks, sir.
I'll watch and learn.

1295
01:12:01,246 --> 01:12:03,180
FLASH: Thanks for the cigar...

1296
01:12:03,248 --> 01:12:05,478
but don't confuse it
with a calumet.

1297
01:12:05,550 --> 01:12:06,539
