and neglect has become...

1365
01:16:29,214 --> 01:16:31,273
widespread
and a growing epidemic.

1366
01:16:31,349 --> 01:16:33,544
The last two to three years
have seen an increase...

1367
01:16:33,618 --> 01:16:35,586
in litigations
against nursing homes...

1368
01:16:35,654 --> 01:16:38,646
and rather sizeable verdicts
across the country.

1369
01:16:38,723 --> 01:16:41,283
As the population of the United
States gets older and older...

1370
01:16:41,359 --> 01:16:44,192
more and more people end up
in nursing homes.

1371
01:16:44,963 --> 01:16:46,225
Moving a parent
to a nursing home...

1372
01:16:46,297 --> 01:16:48,390
is one of life's
most difficult decisions.

1373
01:16:50,802 --> 01:16:52,702
[Keyboard clicking]

1374
01:16:55,507 --> 01:16:57,236
MAN ON TV: L.L., here he is,
700 cubic inches...

1375
01:16:57,308 --> 01:16:59,868
- [Engine revs loudly]
- of fuel-lnjected fury!

1376
01:16:59,944 --> 01:17:03,471
It's the Fred Payne entry,
"Daddy-O", crushin' them buses.

1377
01:17:03,548 --> 01:17:05,675
In the near lane, we've got
Nicky's Nitro supercharged...

1378
01:17:05,750 --> 01:17:08,844
small block, currently points
leader on the circuit...

1379
01:17:08,920 --> 01:17:11,081
Bad breath!
And I don't mean halitosis!

1380
01:17:11,156 --> 01:17:14,523
MAN 2 ON TV: Well, Brad, it's
the giant against the giant killer!

1381
01:17:14,592 --> 01:17:16,753
Nick Thomas has knocked off
more big block opponents...

1382
01:17:16,828 --> 01:17:18,489
this year than anyone else...

1383
01:17:18,563 --> 01:17:22,863
Thanks, honey.
I really appreciate that.

1384
01:17:22,934 --> 01:17:25,926
I'm sorry for being
a pain in the butt.

1385
01:17:28,873 --> 01:17:29,862
Um...

1386
01:17:31,209 --> 01:17:34,007
I mean, going to jail...
and the fight.

1387
01:17:34,079 --> 01:17:36,070
Maybe you learned something
this time.

1388
01:17:36,915 --> 01:17:38,041
Maybe I did.

1389
01:17:40,452 --> 01:17:41,441
I hope so.

1390
01:17:43,021 --> 01:17:45,990
You realize why we didn't
bail you out, don't you?

1391
01:17:46,057 --> 01:17:47,718
Yeah, I know.

1392
01:17:52,363 --> 01:17:53,887
Is something else on your mind?

1393
01:17:58,069 --> 01:18:01,300
Mom, you know that...

1394
01:18:01,372 --> 01:18:03,840
that if anything ever
happens to you, that...

1395
01:18:03,908 --> 01:18:05,341
if you get old or
sick or something...

1396
01:18:05,410 --> 01:18:07,241
that I'll take care of you.

1397
01:18:08,279 --> 01:18:10,042
Honey, nothing's gonna
happen to me.

1398
01:18:10,115 --> 01:18:12,640
I know, knock on wood, but...

1399
01:18:14,285 --> 01:18:17,220
if numb-nuts there ever...
I'm sorry, Floyd...

1400
01:18:17,288 --> 01:18:19,415
if he ever dumps you,
gets rid of you...

1401
01:18:19,491 --> 01:18:21,220
I'll take care of you.

1402
01:18:21,826 --> 01:18:23,726
After I kick his ass.

1403
01:18:23,795 --> 01:18:25,456
We'll both kick his ass.

1404
01:18:26,664 --> 01:18:28,154
I mean it,
whatever happens to you...

1405
01:18:28,233 --> 01:18:31,498
that I'll take care of you.

1406
01:18:31,569 --> 01:18:33,036
I believe you.

1407
01:18:35,774 --> 01:18:38,140
We'll take care of each other.

1408
01:18:39,511 --> 01:18:42,241
[Rain patters, thunder rolls]

1409
01:18:47,352 --> 01:18:49,343
Don't tell me... let me guess!

1410
01:18:50,121 --> 01:18:52,954
I've reached an all-time low!

1411
01:18:53,024 --> 01:18:54,685
Right?

1412
01:18:56,461 --> 01:19:01,091
The film business is a cruel
and shallow money trench...

1413
01:19:01,166 --> 01:19:03,430
a long plastic hallway...

1414
01:19:03,501 --> 01:19:06,698
where thieves
and pimps run wild...

1415
01:19:06,771 --> 01:19:09,535
and good men die like dogs.

1416
01:19:10,441 --> 01:19:13,103
There's also a negative side.

1417
01:19:13,178 --> 01:19:15,578
That's...
That's Hunter S. Thompson!

1418
01:19:15,647 --> 01:19:17,274
I miss him!

1419
01:19:17,348 --> 01:19:20,579
A couple of weeks ago, I was
happily bored and miserable.

1420
01:19:20,652 --> 01:19:22,643
Then you came by
with that kid...

1421
01:19:22,720 --> 01:19:25,245
and tantalized me
with a little hope.

1422
01:19:25,323 --> 01:19:27,951
How dare you toy with my life!

1423
01:19:28,793 --> 01:19:30,818
Get out of here!

1424
01:19:30,895 --> 01:19:34,194
You are so sexy
when you're mad.

1425
01:19:36,401 --> 01:19:37,390
[Thunder rolls]

1426
01:19:38,937 --> 01:19:40,837
Come on in!

1427
01:19:40,905 --> 01:19:42,839
Sin no more.

1428
01:19:48,146 --> 01:19:49,579
[Door creaks]

1429
01:19:49,647 --> 01:19:52,241
You're right about
my daughter, though...

1430
01:19:52,317 --> 01:19:54,410
dumping me like a dog.

1431
01:19:54,485 --> 01:19:57,818
Ah, I was talkin' out of my ass.

1432
01:19:57,889 --> 01:20:00,619
- She didn't dump you.
- The hell she didn't.

1433
01:20:00,692 --> 01:20:02,523
Time I realized it too.

1434
01:20:02,594 --> 01:20:04,221
You know, I oughta be
more like you...

1435
01:20:04,295 --> 01:20:06,786
hate everybody and everything.

1436
01:20:06,865 --> 01:20:08,765
A lot of good it's done me.

1437
01:20:08,833 --> 01:20:11,131
Well, you see the deal
better than most.

1438
01:20:11,202 --> 01:20:12,726
It's a front!

1439
01:20:14,339 --> 01:20:19,470
Flash, you think they really
don't love us anymore?

1440
01:20:19,544 --> 01:20:20,533
Ah...

1441
01:20:21,379 --> 01:20:22,368
Sure they do.

1442
01:20:23,648 --> 01:20:25,707
But they got problems too,
you know...

1443
01:20:25,783 --> 01:20:26,772
distractions and...

1444
01:20:28,253 --> 01:20:30,346
I really miss talking
to my daughter.

1445
01:20:30,421 --> 01:20:32,685
Well, then maybe you
should call her.

1446
01:20:32,757 --> 01:20:34,122
What the hell.

1447
01:20:34,192 --> 01:20:35,523
I think I will.

1448
01:20:37,395 --> 01:20:38,862
So...

1449
01:20:40,598 --> 01:20:41,587
I'm leaving.

1450
01:20:43,067 --> 01:20:45,001
So, we're good.

1451
01:20:45,069 --> 01:20:48,163
Huh? All is forgiven... and all?

1452
01:20:48,239 --> 01:20:50,173
I'll forgive you.

1453
01:20:50,241 --> 01:20:52,368
You're a better man
than I am, Mickey.

1454
01:20:52,443 --> 01:20:54,206
Forgiveness was never
my long suit.

1455
01:20:54,279 --> 01:20:57,476
Oh... I patched it up
with Cameron...

1456
01:20:57,548 --> 01:20:59,015
and the gang at the home.

1457
01:20:59,083 --> 01:21:01,916
Been a busy apologizer, huh?

1458
01:21:01,986 --> 01:21:03,351
[Chuckling] So to speak.

1459
01:21:03,421 --> 01:21:06,390
Well, hope is alive,
the film is back on...

1460
01:21:06,457 --> 01:21:09,483
and Cameron'll be over tomorrow
to help you with the script.

1461
01:21:09,560 --> 01:21:11,653
Great. I like that kid.

1462
01:21:11,729 --> 01:21:13,390
All's right with the world!

1463
01:21:14,499 --> 01:21:15,932
[Door closes]

1464
01:21:19,604 --> 01:21:20,935
[Rain and thunder continue]

1465
01:21:22,507 --> 01:21:25,032
Hope her number's
still the same.

1466
01:21:25,109 --> 01:21:28,237
[Phone beeping]

1467
01:21:33,918 --> 01:21:36,580
Hello? Honey?

1468
01:21:36,654 --> 01:21:39,919
Yeah, this is Daddy.

1469
01:21:39,991 --> 01:21:41,515
Yeah! [Laughs]

1470
01:21:41,592 --> 01:21:44,720
Yeah, I know it's been...
I just wanted to call...

1471
01:21:44,796 --> 01:21:46,354
and see how you're doin',
what...

1472
01:21:46,431 --> 01:21:50,299
Yeah... Oh, you gotta go out.

1473
01:21:50,368 --> 01:21:52,529
Well, yeah... [Laughs]

1474
01:21:52,603 --> 01:21:54,730
I just wanted to talk to you.

1475
01:21:54,806 --> 01:21:56,364
Yeah, I'll-I'll-I'll let you...

1476
01:21:56,441 --> 01:21:58,705
I'll call you
another time, yeah.

1477
01:21:58,776 --> 01:22:01,267
[Chuckles] Bye-bye, honey.

1478
01:22:05,416 --> 01:22:06,906
[Phone beeps]

1479
01:22:21,966 --> 01:22:24,594
[Thunder rumbles...]

1480
01:22:30,141 --> 01:22:32,939
[Typewriter carriage clicks]

1481
01:22:35,680 --> 01:22:39,013
[Typewriter keys tapping...]

1482
01:22:41,819 --> 01:22:43,787
[Choir singing triumphantly]

1483
01:22:46,290 --> 01:22:47,279
[Carriage return dings]

1484
01:22:47,358 --> 01:22:50,293
FLASH: Sabotage
is essential in warfare.

1485
01:22:50,361 --> 01:22:52,295
Brett Raven's ahead of you.
We gotta slow him down.

1486
01:22:52,363 --> 01:22:54,297
CAMERON:
Flash, are you sure about this?

1487
01:22:54,365 --> 01:22:56,595
Are we gonna do this or not?

1488
01:22:56,667 --> 01:22:57,827
You're clear.

1489
01:22:57,902 --> 01:23:00,462
Yeah... Well...

1490
01:23:00,538 --> 01:23:05,305
it's a myth that scripts
are the lifeblood of Hollywood.

1491
01:23:07,378 --> 01:23:09,710
It's gasoline.

1492
01:23:12,250 --> 01:23:13,239
Whoops.

1493
01:23:14,252 --> 01:23:15,549
[Choir singing "Ode to Joy"]

1494
01:23:15,620 --> 01:23:16,814
TEENAGE BO Y: Check it out!

1495
01:23:16,888 --> 01:23:18,116
No more lifeblood.

1496
01:23:21,459 --> 01:23:23,120
- CAMERON: Oh, man.
- MURPHY: Oh, no.

1497
01:23:24,962 --> 01:23:26,452
FLASH: Oh, shit!

1498
01:23:28,966 --> 01:23:29,955
[Explosion]

1499
01:23:31,235 --> 01:23:34,568
[Choir singing finale
to Beethoven's 9th]

1500
01:23:38,709 --> 01:23:41,439
[Orchestra plays triumphant
finale to Beethoven's 9th]

1501
01:23:53,591 --> 01:23:55,218
[General conversations...]

1502
01:23:55,359 --> 01:23:57,919
[Radio plays music...]

1503
01:24:01,132 --> 01:24:02,121
Hey.

1504
01:24:02,200 --> 01:24:04,031
Hey, Cam!

1505
01:24:04,102 --> 01:24:06,127
Whoa, it looks like an
extreme makeover or something...

1506
01:24:06,204 --> 01:24:07,262
going on out there.

1507
01:24:07,338 --> 01:24:09,363
Yeah, they started
to spruce the place up...

1508
01:24:09,440 --> 01:24:12,034
when they heard
about our little project.

1509
01:24:12,110 --> 01:24:14,203
Wonder how they found out
about that?

1510
01:24:14,278 --> 01:24:16,769
- Well, I'm proud of this.
- Yeah? Me too.

1511
01:24:17,882 --> 01:24:21,045
? Ta-taah ?

