1663
01:32:18,329 --> 01:32:19,489
Leaders are born.

1664
01:32:19,563 --> 01:32:20,962
Leaders are made.

1665
01:32:21,031 --> 01:32:22,896
To be a leader,
all you need is followers.

1666
01:32:22,967 --> 01:32:25,629
Have you ever heard the term
"natural-born leader"?

1667
01:32:26,770 --> 01:32:29,102
Why do you have to argue
about everything that I say?

1668
01:32:29,173 --> 01:32:30,970
He's not arguing, Floyd.

1669
01:32:31,041 --> 01:32:33,339
He's topping. He's a topper.

1670
01:32:33,410 --> 01:32:36,709
You know, whatever you say,
he tops. It's a kid thing.

1671
01:32:36,780 --> 01:32:37,906
That's horseshit.

1672
01:32:37,982 --> 01:32:39,609
Cameron, please.

1673
01:32:39,683 --> 01:32:40,809
Sorry, Mom.

1674
01:32:40,884 --> 01:32:42,010
Kids are trying
to find their voice.

1675
01:32:42,086 --> 01:32:43,883
You know, they want to be heard,
they want to be respected.

1676
01:32:43,954 --> 01:32:47,014
It's easy to respect back
when they respect us.

1677
01:32:47,091 --> 01:32:49,059
FLASH: It's one thing to,
uh, demand respect.

1678
01:32:49,126 --> 01:32:51,117
It's another
to command respect.

1679
01:32:51,195 --> 01:32:53,060
[Chuckles] Am I right, Floyd?

1680
01:32:54,465 --> 01:32:55,625
Is he right, Floyd?

1681
01:32:57,835 --> 01:32:58,824
Yeah, right.

1682
01:33:01,038 --> 01:33:03,700
This was
the best Christmas turkey...

1683
01:33:03,774 --> 01:33:06,299
I have eaten
since before I started...

1684
01:33:06,377 --> 01:33:09,744
eating strained prunes
on an irregular basis.

1685
01:33:09,813 --> 01:33:12,748
Thank you, Flash.
It was my pleasure.

1686
01:33:12,816 --> 01:33:13,874
It was great, Mom.

1687
01:33:13,951 --> 01:33:15,816
Well, it deserves a toast,
let me tell you.

1688
01:33:17,221 --> 01:33:18,210
O.K.

1689
01:33:21,492 --> 01:33:22,982
Hey, come on, Floyd.

1690
01:33:23,060 --> 01:33:25,927
You don't have to be a dick
every day of your life.

1691
01:33:25,996 --> 01:33:27,020
Good God, Flash.

1692
01:33:27,097 --> 01:33:28,860
[Laughs] Easy, easy, Flash.

1693
01:33:28,932 --> 01:33:30,297
Eh, I'm just messing with him.
Right, Floyd?

1694
01:33:30,367 --> 01:33:32,528
You and me, we understand
each other, right?

1695
01:33:33,737 --> 01:33:35,136
Yeah, I think we do.

1696
01:33:43,013 --> 01:33:44,275
I'll get coffee and dessert.

1697
01:33:46,884 --> 01:33:49,944
[Choir singing carols]

1698
01:33:59,229 --> 01:34:00,958
Do you have to work
at being an asshole...

1699
01:34:01,031 --> 01:34:02,692
or does it come naturally?

1700
01:34:04,168 --> 01:34:05,635
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1701
01:34:05,703 --> 01:34:08,228
Because it comes
real natural for me.

1702
01:34:08,305 --> 01:34:09,636
Your point is?

1703
01:34:09,707 --> 01:34:11,675
Point is, pal...

1704
01:34:11,742 --> 01:34:13,835
that being an asshole
every day of your life...

1705
01:34:13,911 --> 01:34:15,572
is a dead-end for loneliness.

1706
01:34:15,646 --> 01:34:16,635
One day,
you're gonna wake up...

1707
01:34:16,714 --> 01:34:19,012
